Subject: Re: [T2] Oil Temp Gauge Query

On Sat, 8 Apr 2006, Greg Potts wrote:

> I have a VDO oil temp gauge here that I am interested in installing
> before I go to EveryBus.  There are three wires going into the gauge;
> one is marked as ground, one with a "+" and  one with a G.
>
> Am I correct in assuming this is a powered gauge? I kinda expected it
> would have had a self-powered thermistor like the CHT does.
>
> And finally: Does this gauge care how much wire is between it and the
> sender?

if it is like mine the extra wire is for the instrument light, should be
hooked in with the other instrument lights. I tapped into one of the
lightbulb wires behind the dash.

you have G(round)   +   and  lightbulb.

I have never read anything about the VDO guage having a problem with long
wire runs.

